titles.title: NanoMi - An Open Source Transmission Electron Microscope

descriptions.description: NanoMi is a project towards an open source modular electron microscope. It will allow to assemble transmission electron microscope (TEM) column, scanning TEM (STEM) column or scanning electron microscope (SEM) column. The goal of the NanoMi project is to establish framework for a community development of an electron microscope. Perhaps most important aspect is the license that covers the development: CERN Open Hardware v2, weakly reciprocal for hardware components. https://cern-ohl.web.cern.ch/ and GPL v3 for software (see below)

Experiment 4
P17858_Barium Ion Adduct Mass Spectrometry to Identify Carboxylic Acid Photoproducts from Crude Oil–water Systems Under Solar Irradiation

descriptions.description: Petroleum derived dissolved organic matter (DOMHC) samples were successfully cationized with barium, revealing many [M–H + Ba]+ peaks in both dark and simulated sunlight treatments. The DOMHC samples generated after light exposure exhibited a greater number of [M–H + Ba]+ peaks compared to the dark control. Multiple [M–H + Ba]+ peaks were investigated in the irradiated DOMHC using low resolution MS/MS in order to confirm the presence of diagnostic fragment ions, m/z 139, 155 and 196 in each treatment. Due to the high complexity of the bariated DOMHC mixture, Fourier transform ion cyclotron resonance mass spectrometry (FT-ICR MS/MS) was employed to obtain molecular level information for both irradiated and dark treatments. The irradiated DOMHC treatments had more bariated oxygenated species over a wide range of H/C and O/C when compared to the dark controls. Doubly bariated species were also observed in DOMHC, which provides evidence that photochemistry transforms DOMHC to even more complex mixtures with multiple oxygenations per molecule. This study provides evidence that barium adduct mass spectrometry can be successfully applied to DOMHC screening for the presence of COOHs, both in dark samples and solar irradiated samples. Furthermore, direct evidence and molecular composition of aqueous phase crude oil photoproducts is provided by this technique.

titles.title: Investigating the role of substance use and dependence in planned versus unplanned suicide attempts

descriptions.description: Suicide attempt is defined as a “non-fatal, self-directed, potentially injurious behavior with intent to die as a result of the behavior” (National Institute of Mental Health, 2021). Suicide attempts may be unplanned (i.e., involving little premeditation or preparation) or characterized by extensive forethought and planning (Conner, 2004). Distinct risk factors contribute to planned versus unplanned suicidal behavior: for instance, planned suicide attempts are associated with higher levels of depression and hopelessness, whereas unplanned suicide attempts are often precipitated by an acute stressor, such as interpersonal conflict (Conner, 2004; Kim et al., 2015). A number of studies have investigated substance use and dependence as correlates of planned versus unplanned suicidal behavior with inconsistent findings. For example, studies conducted by Jeon et al. (2010) and Beckman et al. (2019) demonstrate that alcohol use disorder (AUD) and other substance use disorder (SUD) diagnoses are associated with higher risk for impulsive suicide attempt. On the other hand, Kim et al. (2015) found that the prevalence of AUD and other SUDs was significantly higher among individuals with a planned suicide attempt when compared to individuals with an unplanned suicide attempt. It should be noted, however, that Kim et al. (2015) did not address comorbidity of major depressive disorder and SUDs. In the proposed study, we aim to further clarify associations of substance use and dependence with risk for planned versus unplanned suicide attempt. We anticipate that, after controlling for major depression, higher levels of cigarette use, alcohol consumption, heavy drinking, and cannabis use; any use of illicit drugs or misuse of prescription medications; and more severe dependence on nicotine, alcohol, cannabis, and any illicit drug will be associated with elevated risk for unplanned suicide attempt when compared to planned suicide attempt. Beckman, K., Lindh, A. U., Waern, M., Stromsten, L., Renberg, E. S., Runeson, B., & Dahlin, M. (2019). titles.title: P16158_Stream Dissolved Organic Matter in Permafrost Regions Shows Surprising Compositional Similarities but Negative Priming and Nutrient Effects
Study 6. Predictors of Workplace Dilemma Choices

descriptions.description: This research continues to explore how people make judgments on sacrificial workplace scenarios where causing career harm or distress to one person benefits many people or an organization as a whole. In this study, we will collect people's responses to three workplace dilemmas and measure their level of Empathic Concern (Davis, 1980; 1983), Cognitive Reflection Test performance (Frederick, 2005), and Individual vs. Group Focus (Robinson, Joel, & Plaks, 2014). Previously, higher Empathic Concern (EC) and Individual Focus (IF) were shown to predict a higher rate of harm-rejecting decisions, whereas higher Cognitive Reflection Test (CRT) performance and Group Focus (GF) predicted a higher rate of harm-accepting decisions (Conway & Gawronski, 2013; Reynolds & Conway, 2018; Byrd & Conway, 2019; Patil et al., 2020). We are expecting the same relationships to hold for sacrificial workplace scenarios.
